xists": "", "*": "Template:Gondolin"}], "images": ["CdxIconInfoFilled.svg", "Stefan_Meisl_-_Fingolfin's_Tomb.jpg"], "wikitext": {"*": "{{short description|Tomb of Fingolfin overlooking Gondolin}}\n{{Unnamed}}\n[[File:Stefan Meisl - Fingolfin's Tomb.jpg|thumb|right|''Fingolfin's Tomb'' by [[:Category:Images by Stefan Meisl|Stefan Meisl]]]]\n\n'''Fingolfin's cairn''' was the resting place for the body of King [[Fingolfin]], the High King of the [[Noldor]], after his single-handed combat with [[Morgoth]]. It was built upon a mountain top in the [[Echoriad]], to the north of the valley of [[Tumladen]], overlooking the city of [[Gondolin]].\n\n==History==\nAs the forces of Morgoth achieved victory in the [[Dagor Bragollach]], King Fingolfin believed that he was witnessing the end of the Noldor. He rode to the gates of [[Angband]] and challenged the Enemy to battle. Morgoth came forth, they [[Fall of Fingolfin|fought]], and Fingolfin died after wounding his opponent. Morgoth broke the King's body, and was about to cast it to his wolves when the eagle [[Thorondor]] swooped in and snatched the body away.\n\nThe great eagle laid Fingolfin's body upon a mountain above Gondolin. Fingolfin's son, [[Turgon]], then came and piled a high cairn over the body. It is said that no [[Orcs|Orc]] dared to come near the tomb.<ref>{{S|Fingolfin}}</ref>\n\n==Other versions of the legendarium==\nOn a list of names from the 1930s, the cairn is called '''''Sarnas Fingolfin''''' (\"Cairn of Fingolfin\") in [[Noldorin]].<ref>{{LR|A2}}, p. 406</ref>\n\n{{references}}\n\n{{gondolin}}\n\n[[Category:Gondolin]]\n[[Category:Graves and tombs]]"}}}